The design decision is now concrete: preserve the existing upload behavior (an ordinary successor does not inherit a prior correction id), and tighten the legal-owner resolution decision so a correction is resolved only when its exact resolving copy is the unique current tail. That gives locality: workspace, completion, approvals, and readiness already call the same `has_open_blocker` interface. I’m recording this plan before the first test edit.
